definitions.definition: The state of being free from physical or psychological disease , illness , or malfunction ; wellness . [from 11th c.]
examples: Her mental health is really affected by stressful environments.
My granpa still enjoys very good health .

definitions.definition: A state of well-being or balance , often physical but sometimes also mental and social ; the overall level of function of an organism from the cellular (micro) level to the social (macro) level.
examples: The directors are concerned about the financial health of the project.

definitions.definition: ( obsolete ) Cure , remedy . [16th c. (Middle English: 11th–15th c.)]
( countable ) A toast to prosperity . [from 17th c.]
( video games ) The amount of damage an in-game object can withstand before it is destroyed.
examples: The enemies on this level have a lot of health .
